\par }{\b\insrsid3281690 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 1.  A republican socialist party 
\par }{\b\fs20\insrsid3281690 
\par }{\fs20\cf1\insrsid3281690 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 We live in a capitalist market economy, governed through the institutions of a constitutional (or parliamentary) monarchy. These are two important defining character\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
istics of the economics and politics of the United Kingdom. Capitalism concentrates wealth into the hands of a small minority who own and control the bulk of the country\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s productive resources. The constitutional monarchy concentrates political power in t\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 h\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
e hands of a small minority of bureaucrats and politicians. Economic wealth and political power are united in the service of the ruling class.
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 A republican socialist party aims to replace the constitutional monarchy with a democratic secular republic and \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
the capitalist market economy with socialism. The party seeks fundamental change in the distribution of power and wealth in our society. Therefore at the most basic level, a republican socialist party is what it says it is \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 a militant working class party\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 which fights for a democratic republic and socialism.  
\par 
\par }{\b\fs20\cf1\insrsid3281690 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Republicanism and socialism
\par }{\fs20\cf1\insrsid3281690 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 However a definition of a working class party in terms of its historic tasks or aims does not fully capture its essence. The term \hich\f0 \lquote \loch\f0 republican socialist\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0  are not just two 
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 words put next to each other. They form a unity of the opposites. On one side \hich\f0 \lquote \loch\f0 republican\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0  is a political demand. On the other side \hich\f0 \lquote \loch\f0 socialist\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0  refers to the social transformation of the economy. What then is the relationship of politics and economics?
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 We\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 can answer this by reference to Marx and Engels who considered that winning political power was essential for the socialist transformation of society. Their emphasis was on the class struggle as a political struggle to win power. Engels says that \'93
\loch\f0 if one\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 \hich\f0 thing is certain it is that our party and the working class can only come to power in the form of a democratic republic\'94\loch\f0 
.[1]. The democratic republic was seen as a strategic political objective on the road to socialism.
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 This was not accepted by the leader\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ship of German socialism. In the Kaiser\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s Germany the SDP avoided the republican question in the party\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
s Erfurt programme. Engels made this the focal point of his criticism of the draft of the Erfurt Programme. (2)  In 1892 Engels says that \'93\loch\f0 Marx and I, f\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 o\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
r forty years, repeated ad nauseam that for us the democratic republic is the only form in which the struggle between the working class and the capitalist class can first be universalised and then culminate in the decisive victory of the proletariat\'94
\loch\f0  [3] 
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
There is no question of confusing a democratic secular republic with socialism. They are not the same. Yet far from contradicting socialism, the arrival of a democratic republic opens the road to socialism. A democratic republic creates the circumstances 
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 and the means by which the working class can win political power and begin the socialist transformation of society.    
\par }{\b\fs20\cf1\insrsid3281690 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Programme    
\par }{\fs20\cf1\insrsid3281690 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 \hich\f0 This has consequences for the programme. The \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 immediate programme\'94\loch\f0  is the programme with which the party conducts its cu\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
rrent agitation. Whether this is a single programme or is called a \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 minimum\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  or \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 transitional\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  programme doe not matter. If a party formulates its programme in terms of a 
\'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 minimum\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  and \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 maximum\'94\loch\f0  programme, the demand for a democratic republic must be in t\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 h\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
e minimum programme. Therefore a republican socialist party is a working class party that recognises the demand for a democratic secular republic as a strategic goal in the party\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s immediate programme. 
\par 
\par }{\b\fs20\cf1\insrsid3281690 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Russian Social Democratic Labour Party and the Germa\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 n Social Democratic party
\par 
\par }{\fs20\cf1\insrsid3281690 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 The RSDLP and German SDP were the two most important working class parties at the beginning of the 20}{\fs20\cf1\super\insrsid3281690 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 th}{\fs20\cf1\insrsid3281690 
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  century. The former can be identified as a republican socialist party because the demand for a democratic republic was centra\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 l to its minimum programme. The SDP accepted the Kaiser\hich\f0 \rquote 
\loch\f0 s regime. Like the British Labour Party they settled for social reform under a constitutional monarchy. 
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid3281690 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 2.   The Scottish Socialist Party 
\par 
\par }{\fs20\insrsid3281690 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 The SSP considers a Scottish Republic as the road to socia\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
lism. The SSP is therefore a republican socialist party as we have defined it, albeit with a nationalist perspective. The party h}{\fs20\cf1\insrsid3281690 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
as evolved from its early emphasis on Scottish Independence towards greater emphasises on democracy and republicanism. The \'93\loch\f0 Dec\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 \hich\f0 laration of Calton Hill\'94\loch\f0 
 signifies a shift that is taking place even though the issue of nationalism remains. 
